The man convicted of bludgeoning a baby to death in his cot during a home burglary in Victoria two years ago has lodged an appeal against his life sentence.

Harley Hicks, 21, was jailed for life last month after he broke into a Bendigo home in June 2012 and brutally bashed 10-month-old Zayden Veal-Whitting to death.

Hicks, who was 19 at the time, offered no explanation during his trial in June for why he bashed the baby more than 30 times with a homemade baton during the marijuana and ice-fuelled robbery.

